    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen calling `sign place` and `redraw` within `vim.loop` while searching for text, the highlighting disappears.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create `reprorc.lua` with:\r\n    ```lua\r\n    vim.fn.sign_define('foo', { text = '>' })\r\n    vim.loop.timer_start(\r\n      vim.loop.new_timer(),\r\n      0,\r\n      100,\r\n      vim.schedule_wrap(function()\r\n        for i = vim.fn.line('.'), vim.fn.line('$'), 1 do\r\n          vim.fn.sign_place(1, 'bar', 'foo', vim.fn.bufname(), { lnum = i })\r\n        end\r\n        vim.cmd('redraw')\r\n      end)\r\n    )\r\n    ```\r\n2. Create `test.txt` containing:\r\n    ```txt\r\n    abcdef\r\n    abdefg\r\n    ```\r\n3. Launch Neovim: `nvim -u reprorc.lua test.txt`\r\n4. Execute search: `/abd`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/54583542/db2be6d8-f163-48ea-b7c5-910bc630b720\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHighlight the search text incrementally.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/54583542/ca9ffb95-224a-48fb-868c-f1ce7e0e8be3\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.9.5-dev-9+gb20533675\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.0 and archlinux(docker)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nweztern\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo. (tag release-0.9)",
